#. <section class="sutta" id="an9.43"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.43:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.43:0.2"
msgid "5. Sāmaññavagga"
msgstr "5. Similarity"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 43. Kāyasakkhīsutta → kāyasakkhisuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an9.43:0.3"
msgid "43. Kāyasakkhīsutta"
msgstr "43. A Direct Witness"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: Kāyasakkhī → kāyasakkhi (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "an9.43:1.1"
msgid "“‘Kāyasakkhī, kāyasakkhī’ti, āvuso, vuccati."
msgstr "“Reverend, they speak of a person called ‘direct witness’."

msgctxt "an9.43:1.2"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso, kāyasakkhī vutto bhagavatā”ti?"
msgstr "What is the direct witness that the Buddha spoke of?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an9.43:2.1"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"“First, take a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures … enters "
"and remains in the first absorption."

# BB’s translation is so artificial here it strains to be English.
msgctxt "an9.43:2.2"
msgid "Yathā yathā ca tadāyatanaṃ tathā tathā naṃ kāyena phusitvā viharati."
msgstr "They meditate directly experiencing that dimension in every way."

msgctxt "an9.43:2.3"
msgid "Ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, kāyasakkhī vutto bhagavatā pariyāyena. (1)"
msgstr ""
"To this extent the Buddha spoke of the direct witness in a qualified sense."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.452"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an9.43:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ "
"…"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who, as the placing of the mind and keeping it "
"connected are stilled, enters and remains in the second absorption …"

msgctxt "an9.43:3.2"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …"
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "an9.43:3.3"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "fourth absorption."

msgctxt "an9.43:3.4"
msgid "Yathā yathā ca tadāyatanaṃ tathā tathā naṃ kāyena phusitvā viharati."
msgstr "They meditate directly experiencing that dimension in every way."

msgctxt "an9.43:3.5"
msgid "Ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, kāyasakkhī vutto bhagavatā pariyāyena. (2–4.)"
msgstr ""
"To this extent the Buddha spoke of the direct witness in a qualified sense."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an9.43:4.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā "
"paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti "
"ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who, going totally beyond perceptions of form, "
"with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions "
"of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the "
"dimension of infinite space."

msgctxt "an9.43:4.2"
msgid "Yathā yathā ca tadāyatanaṃ tathā tathā naṃ kāyena phusitvā viharati."
msgstr "They meditate directly experiencing that dimension in every way."

msgctxt "an9.43:4.3"
msgid ""
"Ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, kāyasakkhī vutto bhagavatā pariyāyena … pe …. (5–8.)"
msgstr ""
"To this extent the Buddha spoke of the direct witness in a qualified sense. "
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who enters and remains in the dimension of "
"infinite consciousness … nothingness … neither perception nor non-perception "
"…"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an9.43:5.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma "
"saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati, paññāya cassa disvā āsavā "
"parikkhīṇā honti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who, going totally beyond the dimension of "
"neither perception nor non-perception, enters and remains in the cessation "
"of perception and feeling. And, having seen with wisdom, their defilements "
"come to an end."

msgctxt "an9.43:5.2"
msgid "Yathā yathā ca tadāyatanaṃ tathā tathā naṃ kāyena phusitvā viharati."
msgstr "They meditate directly experiencing that dimension in every way."

msgctxt "an9.43:5.3"
msgid "Ettāvatāpi kho, āvuso, kāyasakkhī vutto bhagavatā nippariyāyenā”ti. (9)"
msgstr ""
"To this extent the Buddha spoke of the direct witness in a definitive sense.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.43:5.4"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
